data.text:
Jack Dempsey has not been included in the Australia squad for their autumn fixtures, paving the way for the Glasgow Warriors No 8 to be called up by Scotland tomorrow.

Although the 28-year-old former Waratahs player has 14 Wallabies caps, the most recent of them came on October 11 2019, meaning he has now served the three-year stand-down period stipulated in the new World Rugby regulations for players who wish to represent another nation for which they qualify through bloodline.

Gregor Townsend names his autumn squad on Wednesday, and it is widely expected that Dempsey will be part of it, which would put him in line to make a dramatic start to the second chapter of his Test career when Australia come to Murrayfield on
